---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'May 2026';
---
<BaseLayout title="Accessibility" description="EduRankAI's accessibility statement, conformance status, and how to report accessibility issues.">

  <section class="px-[5vw] pt-16 md:pt-24 pb-10 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <p class="text-[0.62rem] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-burn font-bold mb-6">Accessibility</p>
    <h1 class="font-display text-[clamp(2rem,5vw,3.5rem)] font-semibold text-ink leading-[1.05] tracking-tight mb-6">
      Accessibility <em class="italic text-burn font-medium">statement.</em>
    </h1>
    <p class="text-[0.85rem] font-mono text-ink-soft">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
  </section>

  <section class="px-[5vw] pb-12 max-w-3xl mx-auto prose-content">
    <div class="space-y-8 text-[0.95rem] text-ink-soft leading-[1.85]">

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-[1.4rem] font-semibold text-ink mb-3">Our commitment</h2>
        <p>
          EduRankAI is committed to making our website, products, and applicant portal usable by everyone — including people with disabilities. Accessibility is part of how we measure quality, not an afterthought.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-[1.4rem] font-semibold text-ink mb-3">Conformance target</h2>
        <p>
          We aim to conform to the <strong class="text-ink">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA</strong>. These guidelines explain how to make web content accessible to people with a wide range of disabilities — including visual, auditory, motor, and cognitive.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-[1.4rem] font-semibold text-ink mb-3">What we have done</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
          <li>Semantic HTML structure with clear heading hierarchy on every page.</li>
          <li>Skip-to-main-content link available on every page (press Tab on page load).</li>
          <li>Visible focus indicators on all interactive elements.</li>
          <li>Color contrast tuned for readability across the site's primary palette.</li>
          <li>Form fields labelled and associated with their controls.</li>
          <li>Mobile touch targets sized to at least 44×44 pixels.</li>
          <li>Reduced-motion preferences respected for our scroll and entrance animations.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-[1.4rem] font-semibold text-ink mb-3">Known limitations</h2>
        <p>
          We are still working on a few items. If you encounter any of these, please let us know and we'll prioritise:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 mt-2">
          <li>Some embedded third-party content (videos, live class iframes) may not meet our standards.</li>
          <li>Older blog posts or PDFs uploaded before our policy was formalised may have inconsistent alt text.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-[1.4rem] font-semibold text-ink mb-3">Report an issue</h2>
        <p>
          If you experience a barrier or have a suggestion, email <a href="mailto:connect@edurankai.in?subject=Accessibility%20feedback" class="text-burn hover:underline font-semibold">connect@edurankai.in</a> with the URL, the issue, and the assistive technology you were using. We aim to acknowledge within 2 business days and resolve substantive issues within 14 days.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-[1.4rem] font-semibold text-ink mb-3">Assessment approach</h2>
        <p>
          This statement reflects ongoing self-evaluation combined with automated checks. We plan to engage an external accessibility audit once the next product cycle ships.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
